## 5.1.1 — 2026-04-29

### Bugfix: prevent OOM-cascade reaping user's tmux scope

A `codemap` invocation without `--dir` (defaulting to `$HOME` or `~/Desktop`)
was walking 192,000+ files and ballooning to ~50 GB heap before the kernel
OOM-killed it. Because the process ran inside a systemd `tmux-spawn-*.scope`
cgroup, the kernel/systemd then SIGKILL'd every other process in the same
scope — including the user's tmux session. Verified incident
2026-04-29 23:18:39 UTC on Charles's mater workstation.

Three guards added:

1. **CLI refuses to default-scan `$HOME`.** Running `codemap <action>` from
   the user's home directory without `--dir` now exits with code 2 and a
   helpful error pointing at `--dir <smaller_path>`. Override with
   `CODEMAP_NO_FILE_LIMIT=1`.
2. **Hard file-count cap (50,000 supported files).** `walk_dir` short-circuits
   when the cap is reached and `scan_single_dir` returns
   `ScanError("...hit the safety cap of 50000...")`. Override with the same
   env var.
3. **Warning at 10,000 files.** `scan_single_dir` prints a stderr warning
   suggesting `--dir` scoping, but proceeds.

Implementation: `codemap-core/src/scanner.rs` (`walk_dir` now returns `bool`
and accepts `file_cap`; `scan_single_dir` reads `CODEMAP_NO_FILE_LIMIT`),
`codemap-cli/src/main.rs` ($HOME-equality refuse + cwd-default note).

No API change to napi bindings or any action; existing integration tests
unaffected.

[2026-04-30] fix: 5.1.2 — root-cause SKIP_DIRS, prevent vendored-tree AST parse
  source: post-mortem of 5.1.1 incident — 50 GB heap was driven by codemap
  AST-parsing every file in every project's `.venv/lib/python3.13/site-packages/`
  tree. SKIP_DIRS only knew about `node_modules .git dist build .codemap target`
  (Node + Rust + git), so a Python venv was indistinguishable from user code.
  Smoke test on mater: `~/Desktop` walk dropped 6,888 → 4,237 files (-39%) once
  `.venv venv __pycache__ vendor .next .nuxt .tox .pytest_cache .mypy_cache
  .ruff_cache site-packages bower_components Pods .gradle .svelte-kit .vercel
  .turbo .parcel-cache .cache .nyc_output .idea .vscode .hg .svn out coverage
  jspm_packages` were added.

  This is the actual fix for the 2026-04-29 OOM cascade. The 5.1.1 guards
  (50K hard cap, $HOME refuse, 10K warning) remain as belt-and-suspenders
  for genuinely large user codebases, but should no longer trigger in
  normal use.

  Implementation: `codemap-core/src/scanner.rs` (SKIP_DIRS expanded with
  ecosystem-wide dep/cache/build conventions). New regression test
  `test_skip_dirs_exclude_dep_trees` materializes 12 vendored/cached files
  alongside one user file and asserts only the user file lands in the graph.

