[2026-04-30] feat: 5.15.3 — APK / Android analysis (v1) (#43)
  source: 5.14.0 task #43, deferred until last because of scope.
  Shipped here as a focused v1 covering structure + permissions
  but deferring DEX bytecode disasm.

  Two new EntityKinds:
    - AndroidPackage (kind: "apk") — APK package node. Edges:
      apk → permission (declared in manifest), apk → bin_func (DEX
      methods, when DEX disasm lands).
    - Permission (kind: "permission") — Android permission. Killer
      query target: meta-path "permission->method" answers "what
      code uses CAMERA permission?" (when DEX bytecode method
      extraction ships).

  New module: src/actions/apk.rs (~330 LOC). New action:
  apk-info <apk-file> (aliases: apk, android).

  Implementation:
    - Walk ZIP local-file headers (PK\x03\x04). No actual inflate
      — we list entry names, only extract uncompressed entries
      verbatim. Real APKs deflate-compress AndroidManifest.xml so
      permission extraction gracefully degrades when manifest is
      compressed.
    - Categorize entries: DEX files (classes*.dex), manifest,
      resources.arsc, native libs (lib/**/*.so), signing files
      (META-INF/*.RSA / *.SF).
    - Best-effort permission extraction: pattern-scan the manifest
      bytes for "android.permission." prefixes in both UTF-8 and
      UTF-16 encodings. Catches permissions when manifest is
      stored uncompressed (rare but happens) and skips otherwise.
    - Flag dangerous permissions (CAMERA, READ_SMS, FINE_LOCATION,
      etc.) with ⚠ in the report.

  v1 limits (intentional):
    - No deflate decompression (would need flate2 dep). Compressed
      manifest ⇒ no permissions extracted; structure still listed.
    - No DEX bytecode disasm. Permission → method edges deferred
      until a follow-up adds Dalvik opcode parsing.
    - No binary AXML schema parser. Real AXML is a length-prefixed
      string-pool format; pattern-scanning catches the common case
      but misses obfuscated namespaces.

  Tests: 180 passing (was 177). +3 apk unit tests covering ZIP
  magic detection, dangerous permission lookup, UTF-8 permission
  pattern extraction.

  Action count: 158 → 159 (+1: apk-info).
  Total EntityKinds: 28 (up from 20 at session start).

