[2026-04-30] feat: 5.16.0 — recon-artifact parsers (#49)
  source: post-SBM-recon (main4) gap analysis. Charles affirmed
  "if you build an active crawler codemap isn't really codemap
  anymore" — so this release stays strictly pure-static. Each
  parser consumes a captured artifact (file the user named
  explicitly); never makes network requests.

  Four new actions, no new EntityKinds (reuse HttpEndpoint, Compiler,
  Cert from earlier releases):

    - robots-parse <robots.txt> — classify each Disallow/Allow
      rule (admin / sensitive / api / auth / search / asset /
      generic), promote each path to an HttpEndpoint with
      attrs[discovered_via=robots, category=...]. Flag leaky
      rules (admin/sensitive/api categories — robots that
      *advertise* sensitive paths). Capture Sitemap directives
      separately.
    - web-sitemap-parse <sitemap.xml> — extract every <loc>,
      promote to HttpEndpoint nodes, group URLs by path pattern
      with `{ID}` substitution for numeric/UUID segments. Detects
      ID-enumerable patterns (the killer "this sitemap exposes
      a complete enumeration" finding from main4).
    - web-fingerprint <html-or-har> — Wappalyzer-style tech
      detection via 50+ signature rules covering CMSes (WordPress,
      Drupal, Ghost, Sanity, Strapi), backend frameworks (JHipster,
      Spring Boot, Django, Rails, Laravel, ASP.NET, FastAPI,
      Phoenix), frontend (Next.js, React, Vue, Angular, Svelte,
      Nuxt, Gatsby, Remix), servers (nginx/Apache/IIS/Caddy/
      OpenResty), CDNs (Cloudflare/CloudFront/Fastly/Akamai/
      Vercel/Netlify), libs (jQuery, lodash, Bootstrap, Tailwind,
      Algolia, Elasticsearch), analytics (GA, Segment, Mixpanel).
      Each match registers a Compiler node with category +
      anchor count + confidence (25-100 based on hits).
    - crt-parse <crt.sh-json> — parses crt.sh ?output=json
      response, extracts subdomains from name_value (split on \n,
      strip wildcards), tracks earliest not_before per host,
      registers HttpEndpoint per host + Cert per issuer.

  Implementation: src/actions/recon.rs (~590 LOC). All four
  parsers operate on captured artifacts. User does the curl
  themselves; codemap parses the result. Single-file actions —
  no recursion, no crawling, no network. Same line wget draws.

  Live verification on the SBM recon artifacts (/tmp/sbm-recon/):
    - robots-parse → 24 rules classified, 8 leaky paths flagged
      (/api/audits/, /api/logs/, /api/users/, /management/,
      /v2/api-docs/, etc.), 5 multi-tenant sitemap directives
      captured (sbm/gabar/isba/inbar/nebar — Zeekbeek platform).
    - web-sitemap-parse on sbm_sitemap.xml → 47,229 URLs
      extracted, ID-enumerable pattern /lawyer/{ID} auto-detected
      → exactly the killer finding from main4.
    - web-fingerprint on vendor bundle → React (3 anchors, 75%
      confidence) + Google Analytics caught honestly.

  Tests: 186 passing (was 180). +6 recon unit tests covering
